All soups come with a side of bread for dipping, which I love.
I am also nuts about the Nuts About Berries salad, the cinnamon almonds are genius!
I've also tried their pulled pork, Asian BBQ pork, and Turkey Bacon Avocado sandwiches.
The sandwiches are not gourmet or the best sandwiches in the area, but they are pretty good, especially when they are coupled with soup and/or salad.
To top everything off, everyone gets a chocolate covered strawberry with their meal!
What?!
How can this tiny gesture make me so happy?
I don't know, but it does!
I've heard great things about their other desserts, but haven't tried any yet.
This is a fantastic lunch option any day of the week, except Sundays, because they are closed on Sundays.

